<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05017g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05017g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05017g"> 17(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> God Who Knows asks information <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n05017g"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"> The Lord complained that the sin of Sodom and Gomorrah was &ldquo;very grievous,&rdquo; and said that the great cry of it had reached him in heaven. Being much concerned about their &ldquo;goings on,&rdquo; he had resolved to drop down and see for himself if they were really as bad as he suspected. &ldquo;If not,&rdquo; said he, &ldquo;I will know.&rdquo; Thus in the Old Testament, <mark>God, who knows everything, is frequently seeking information</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Lot&apos;s Wife] 85</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
